<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbc6d8c90-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s3058dd"><num value="3058dd">§ 3058dd.</num><heading> Technical assistance</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbc6d8c91-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s3058dd/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Other agencies</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In carrying out the provisions of this subchapter, the Assistant Secretary may request the technical assistance and cooperation of such Federal entities as may be appropriate.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbc6d8c92-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s3058dd/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Assistant Secretary</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Assistant Secretary shall provide technical assistance and training (by contract, grant, or otherwise) to persons and entities that administer programs established under this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idbc6d8c93-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/73/tVII/s763">Pub. L. 89–73, title VII, § 763</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/102/375/tVII/s707">Pub. L. 102–375, title VII, § 707</ref>, <date date="1992-09-30">Sept. 30, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/1291">106 Stat. 1291</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/103/171/s3/a/11">Pub. L. 103–171, § 3(a)(11)</ref>, (13), <date date="1993-12-02">Dec. 2, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/1990">107 Stat. 1990</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
